\title{Tree authorship}
\author{samueltoth}
\author{fredrikbakke}

\p{Trees in the forest can be assigned authorship by using the
\code{\statverb \author{authorname} \stopverb} command, where \code{authorname}
is a reference to another tree, which should have the \code{person} taxon and
be located in the \code{trees/people/} subdirectory. Trees can also be given
\em{contributors} with the \code{\startverb \contributor{} \stopverb} taxon.}

\p{An author is someone who has either defined the tree itself, or has made a
defining contribution, e.g., if they provided the main definition or proved the
main theorem of a module then they are also an author. Otherwise if they've made
smaller contributions they are a "\em{contributor}".}
